  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed new fourth floor level, by reason of its excessive and uncharacteristic design, scale, bulk, massing and prominent siting due to its almost full site coverage, sharp roofline, poor materials and poor architectural treatment, would represent a dominant, discordant and incongruous form of development within the locality, diminishing the quality and character of the area and the setting of the nearby Angel and Chapel Market/Penton Street Conservation Areas. The development is therefore contrary to the NPPF 2019, policies 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2016, policy CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies 2013 and the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide 2017."
